metadata.dc:description: Penile fracture with urethral laceration usually presents with pain and haematoma, detumescence, erectile failure and blood loss through urethral meatus. We describe the third published case of urethrocavernous fistula following blunt penile trauma sustained durind sexual intercourse.
metadata.dc:title: Fistula uretrocavernosa por fractura penena.
[Urethrocavernous fistula due to penile fracture].
